# preview / mock data (temporary, removable, isolated)

Purpose: render the full site via `npm run dev` before Supabase, Stripe, or real images exist. Confine ALL mock content to exactly two locations so it deletes in one step:
- `lib/mock-products.ts` — the mock product + variant data.
- `public/placeholders/` — placeholder images.

Fallback rule (auto-supersede): the catalog and product-detail data functions query Supabase first. If `NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL` is unset OR the query returns zero rows, fall back to `lib/mock-products.ts`. Once real ingested rows exist, mock data never renders. No env flag toggling; real data always wins.

Mock dataset: ~3 products per gender. Include at least one women-only type (`anklets`) plus typical types (`bracelets`, `rings`, `necklaces`, etc.) so the per-gender asymmetry shows.

**Variant coverage (required):**
- At least **one multi-variant product** with 2–3 colors, varied image counts per color, one color **sold out** (`stock: 0`) to exercise cross-out toggle and auto-select-first-in-stock behavior.
- Several **single-variant products** (one color / default only) to confirm the color toggle is hidden.
- Each variant mirrors a real row shape: `color`, ordered `images` array, `stock`, `is_default`. Product row holds shared fields (`name`, `material`, `properties` with baseline merged, `price_fils`, `description`). Public mock selects expose variant `available` boolean, never stock count.

Placeholder images: simple labeled placeholders (solid-fill SVG/PNG). Paths follow ingest layout, e.g. `public/placeholders/{gender}/{accessory_type}/{folder_index}/{color}/1.svg` for multi-variant, or `.../{folder_index}/1.svg` for single-variant default. No model-men/model-women frame assets. These are the ONLY images to fabricate.

Checkout in mock mode: do not create a live Stripe session for mock variants (see the checkout rule).
